Mean Intersection-Over-Union is a common evaluation metric for semantic image segmentation, which first computes the IOU for each semantic class and then computes the average over classes. IOU is defined as follows: IOU = true_positive / (true_positive + false_positive + false_negative). The predictions are accumulated in a confusion matrix, weighted by sample_weight and the metric is then calculated from it.
trans-unit.target: Mean Intersection-Over-Union是语义图像分割的常用评估指标，它首先计算每个语义类的IOU，然后计算所有类的平均值。 IOU的定义如下：IOU = true_positive /（true_positive + false_positive + false_negative）。预测将累积在混淆矩阵中，并由 sample_weight 加权，然后从中计算度量。

trans-unit.source: Mean Intersection-Over-Union is a common evaluation metric for semantic image segmentation, which first computes the IOU for each semantic class and then computes the average over classes. IOU is defined as follows: IOU = true_positive / (true_positive + false_positive + false_negative). The predictions are accumulated in a confusion matrix, weighted by weights, and mIOU is then calculated from it.
trans-unit.target: Mean Intersection-Over-Union是语义图像分割的常用评估指标，它首先计算每个语义类的IOU，然后计算所有类的平均值。IOU的定义如下：IOU = true_positive /（true_positive + false_positive + false_negative）。预测值会存储在混淆矩阵中，并按 weights ，然后从中计算出mIOU。

trans-unit.source: Measures the probability error in discrete classification tasks in which each class is independent and not mutually exclusive. For instance, one could perform multilabel classification where a picture can contain both an elephant and a dog at the same time.
trans-unit.target: 测量离散分类任务中的概率误差,其中每个类别是独立的,而不是相互排斥的。例如,我们可以进行多标签分类,一张图片可以同时包含一头大象和一条狗。

trans-unit.source: Measures the probability error in discrete classification tasks in which the classes are mutually exclusive (each entry is in exactly one class). For example, each CIFAR-10 image is labeled with one and only one label: an image can be a dog or a truck, but not both.
trans-unit.target: 衡量离散分类任务中的概率误差,在这种情况下,类是相互排斥的(每个条目正好属于一个类)。例如,每张CIFAR-10图像都有一个且仅有一个标签:一张图像可以是一只狗或一辆卡车,但不能同时是狗和卡车。

trans-unit.source: Mel Frequency Cepstral Coefficients are a way of representing audio data that's been effective as an input feature for machine learning. They are created by taking the spectrum of a spectrogram (a 'cepstrum'), and discarding some of the higher frequencies that are less significant to the human ear. They have a long history in the speech recognition world, and https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mel-frequency_cepstrum is a good resource to learn more.
trans-unit.target: 梅尔频率倒谱系数是一种表示音频数据的方法，该数据已有效地用作机器学习的输入功能。它们是通过获取频谱图（“倒谱”）的频谱并丢弃一些对人耳不太重要的较高频率而创建的。他们在语音识别领域拥有悠久的历史，并且https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mel-frequency_cepstrum是了解更多信息的好资源。

trans-unit.source: MobileNet is a general architecture and can be used for multiple use cases. Depending on the use case, it can use different input layer size and different width factors. This allows different width models to reduce the number of multiply-adds and thereby reduce inference cost on mobile devices.
trans-unit.target: MobileNet是一个通用架构,可以用于多种用例。根据不同的用例,它可以使用不同的输入层大小和不同的宽度因子。这使得不同宽度的模型可以减少乘加次数,从而降低移动设备上的推理成本。

trans-unit.source: MobileNetV2 is a general architecture and can be used for multiple use cases. Depending on the use case, it can use different input layer size and different width factors. This allows different width models to reduce the number of multiply-adds and thereby reduce inference cost on mobile devices.
trans-unit.target: MobileNetV2是一个通用的架构,可以用于多种用例。根据不同的用例,它可以使用不同的输入层大小和不同的宽度因子。这使得不同宽度的模型可以减少乘加次数,从而降低移动设备上的推理成本。

trans-unit.source: MobileNetV2 is very similar to the original MobileNet, except that it uses inverted residual blocks with bottlenecking features. It has a drastically lower parameter count than the original MobileNet. MobileNets support any input size greater than 32 x 32, with larger image sizes offering better performance.
trans-unit.target: MobileNetV2与原来的MobileNet非常相似,只是它采用了具有瓶颈功能的倒余块。它的参数数比原来的MobileNet大幅减少。MobileNets支持任何大于32×32的输入尺寸,较大的图像尺寸具有更好的性能。

trans-unit.source: MobileNets support any input size greater than 32 x 32, with larger image sizes offering better performance. The number of parameters and number of multiply-adds can be modified by using the alpha parameter, which increases/decreases the number of filters in each layer. By altering the image size and alpha parameter, all 16 models from the paper can be built, with ImageNet weights provided.
trans-unit.target: MobileNets支持任何大于32 x 32的输入大小，较大的图像大小可提供更好的性能。可以通过使用 alpha 参数来修改参数的数量和乘加的数量，该参数增加/减少每层中的滤波器的数量。通过更改图像大小和 alpha 参数，可以使用提供的ImageNet权重构建纸张上的所有16种模型。
